GMATWiz - GMAT Focus Quant (Problem Solving) lesson library
============================================================

WHAT THIS IS
------------
Authored lesson content for the Quantitative Reasoning section of the
GMAT Focus Edition (Problem Solving only: arithmetic + algebra; no
geometry, no Data Sufficiency - per PRD Section 5). Every topic is a
self-contained lesson built on the same schema and the same evidence-
based learning model. Content is authored (OfficialFlag=false); scarce
official questions are reserved as late-stage checkpoints (PRD 13).

PEDAGOGICAL MODEL (PRD Section 2 + Section 9; skills applied)
------------
1. Retrieval-practice OPENING (lesson-opening-designer skill):
   - Do-Now retrieval from memory targeting the exact prerequisites
     today's topic depends on (Rosenshine Principle 1; Agarwal 2012).
   - Prior-knowledge BRIDGE that states the connection explicitly
     (Ausubel advance organiser; Marzano).
   - LEARNING INTENTION describing learning, not activity (Hattie),
     plus student-facing success criteria.
2. Mastery loop I DO -> WE DO -> YOU DO (Archer; PRD 9.2):
   - I do:  one worked example with think-aloud reasoning.
   - We do: 2-3 guided items with faded scaffolds + immediate feedback.
   - You do: 3-5 independent, new exam-style items.
3. APPLICATION-FIRST (SPOV2, PRD Section 2): in you_do, the explanation
   is withheld until AFTER an attempt (reveal_explanation_after_attempt).
   Application creates competence; lessons only create confidence.
4. ERROR LOG (required, PRD Section 10): every miss carries error-type
   tags (content gap / reasoning flaw / timing / careless / trap) and
   becomes spaced re-practice.
5. MASTERY = >=85% correct on new/held-out items across >=2 spaced
   sessions with delay (PRD Section 9.2) - not flashcard recall alone.

SCHEMA (see schema.json - JSON Schema draft-07)
------------
Each <slug>.json has: schema_version, topic_id, slug, title, section,
question_type, domain, exam, estimated_minutes, prerequisites,
learning_objectives, pedagogical_model, opening{do_now, retrieval_starter,
prior_knowledge_bridge, learning_intention, success_criteria,
opening_script}, i_do, we_do[], you_do[], mastery_check, citations[], tags[].

Every practice item (i_do, we_do[], you_do[], held-out samples) maps 1:1
onto the PRD Section 8 'GMAT PS' notetype so the app can import directly:
  Stem=stem  OptionA..E=options.A..E  Correct=correct  Explanation=explanation
  Topic=topic  Difficulty=difficulty  Source=source  OfficialFlag=official_flag

